<p>I am trying to log into mysql using SSH using this command:</p>  <pre><code>mysql -u username -p -h hostname </code></pre>  <p>Where 'username' and 'hostname' and placeholders for the real params. However, the above gives an error :</p>  <pre><code>ERROR 1045 (28000): Access denied for user 'username'@'vps-xxxxxx.xxxx.com' (using password: YES) </code></pre>  <p>Why is it appending the "@vps-xx...." with the remote server username?</p>